# Security rules

- Never commit secrets, API keys, private keys, certificates, passwords, real tokens, or production credentials.
- Do not log sensitive payment, user, or seller KYC data.
- Do not expose full error details to users for payment/delivery/provider failures.
- Treat env files as local-only unless explicitly using .env.example.
- If a secret-looking value is found in code, stop and report it before editing.